---
/**
 * Introduction, Quick Start, and File Location sections of the v1 spec.
 */
---

<section id="introduction" class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The <strong class="text-white">Cookie Consent Declaration</strong> is an open standard
    that allows websites to declare their cookie usage in a machine-readable format. By
    placing a JSON file at a well-known URL, websites enable browsers, extensions, and
    automated agents to read and act on cookie consent preferences without requiring
    user interaction with consent popups.
  </p>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
    Think of it as <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">robots.txt</code>
    for cookie consent. Just as <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">robots.txt</code>
    tells crawlers what they can access, <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">cookie-consent.json</code>
    tells tools what cookies a site uses and how to manage consent programmatically.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="quick-start" class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">2. Quick Start</h2>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The minimal valid file requires just two fields:
  </p>
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-surface-light p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4">
    <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-muted">{`{
  "version": "1.0",
  "categories": ["essential"]
}`}</code></pre>
  </div>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
    Place this file at <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">
    https://yoursite.com/.well-known/cookie-consent.json</code> and you are compliant
    with the standard.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="file-location" class="mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">3. File Location</h2>
  <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The declaration file <strong class="text-white">must</strong> be served at:
  </p>
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-surface-light p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4">
    <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-primary">/.well-known/cookie-consent.json</code></pre>
  </div>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted space-y-2">
    <li>Content-Type must be <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">application/json</code></li>
    <li>Must be accessible without authentication</li>
    <li>Must be served over HTTPS in production</li>
    <li>Should include appropriate CORS headers for cross-origin access</li>
    <li>File size should not exceed 10 KB</li>
  </ul>
</section>
